The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	New Delhi, Feb. 19: Delhi police today filed a chargesheet against arrested Maoist ideologue Khobad Ghandy.          
	The 700-page document says Ghandy has been booked under the Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act and in several other cases for cheating and impersonation under the IPC. It says Ghandy has been involved in cases of Naxalite violence across the country and has been part of anti-national activities.                  
	Mumbai: A Mumbai court has begun the trial of actor Shiney Ahuja, accused of raping his domestic help in June. Ahuja, out on bail, was present in court on Friday. The court has asked him to stay out of Mumbai so that he could not exert any influence on the victim.                   
	Surat (PTI): Three youths have been sentenced to life by a district court for raping a 17-year-old girl in a moving car in June 2009. They have been fined Rs 3 lakh each of which Rs 2 lakh would be given to the victim. Two of the accused, Sahid Sayyed and Tariq Sayyed, are sons of policemen.                  
	New Delhi : The Centre on Friday announced the C.V.Raman International Fellowship programme to bring 416 scientists each year from Africa for short-term positions in Indian research units. It will be open to post-doctoral researchers, mid-career scientists and professors.                  
	 Mumbai (PTI): A fire broke out on Friday at a shopping centre in Borivali, killing a fire officer. Pradeep Zagade, an assistant station officer, died of suffocation while dowsing the blaze at the Goyal Shopping Centre even though he was wearing a breathing set.                                                                                                                                              
